<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-10-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-10-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="263" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d263">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hart</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-10-06"><hi rend="italic">October 6,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 427.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Acknowledging the receipt of your No. 650,
                            of August 23 last, in the matter of expropriation by the Colombian
                            military authorities of the property of American citizens, I refer, in
                            response, to the Department’s cablegram of August 27. The treaty
                            provision and the cablegram referred to cover the question
                            generally.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>